    "After sojourns at Wilhelm Humboldt University in Berlin and the University of Munich, he was granted a doctorate from Leipzig in 1923/4 under <a href=\"/pinderw\">Wilhelm Pinder</a>.": [],
    "Other scholars under who Hermann studied included <a href=\"/goldschmidta\">Adolph Goldschmidt</a>, <a href=\"/jantzenh\">Hans Jantzen</a> and <a href=\"/wolfflinh\">Heinrich W\u00f6lfflin</a> His formal career began as assistant keeper of prints and drawings at the Staatliches Kunstgewerbemuseum in Berlin in 1925.": [],
    "He served there, advancing to keeper, until 1933 when he fled to London because of Jewish persecution.": [],
    "Hermann pursued a career as a manufacturing entrepreneur until 1950 when he returned to architectural scholarship.": [],
    "During this period he produced some of his most notable works, including monographs on <a href=\"/semperg\">Gottfried Semper</a> and architectural theory in general.</p>": []
